It is recommended to implement minimum and standard requirements for segregation and storage of solid waste pending collections and their final disposal to the dumpsite, as follows:

Implement the establishment of Solid Waste Management Eco-Park;

Separate containers/ receptacles  for all types of wastes shall be maintained from all sources;

These containers must be properly marked or identified for on-site collections such as  compostable, non- recyclable, recyclable,  special waste and/or any other classification as may be determined by the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board; and,

Maintain receptacles and Materials Recovery Facility for temporary placement of solid wastes.

